article.description: Freshman Ledarrius Brewer scored 34 points with seven 3-pointers -- both career-highs -- and Southeast Missouri State jumped ahead early to defeat Eastern Illinois 80-73 Thursday night.
article.headline: Brewer scores 34, paces Southeast Missouri St. to 80-73 win
article.linkText: Brewer scores 34, paces Southeast Missouri St. to 80-73 win
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. -- Freshman Ledarrius Brewer scored 34 points with seven 3-pointers -- both career-highs -- and Southeast Missouri State jumped ahead early to defeat Eastern Illinois 80-73 Thursday night. Brewer, 11 of 18 from the floor and 7 of 10 from distance, is the second Southeast Missouri State player to score 30 in a game this season, and the first to make seven 3s in a game since Feb. 28, 2013. Southeast Missouri State led by 21 late in the first half, but Eastern Illinois mounted a comeback that pulled the Panthers into a 61-61 tie when Mack Smith hit a 35-foot 3-pointer with seven minutes remaining. The Redhawks surged ahead on an 8-2 run, capped by a Milos Vranes 3-pointer from the corner, to lead 69-63 with 3:49 remaining. Vranes finished with 11 points, Denzel Mahoney added 13 with 10 rebounds for Southeast Missouri State (13-15, 7-8 Ohio Valley Conference). Montell Goodwin scored 18 to lead Eastern Illinois (9-17, 5-10), Muusa Dama added 17 with 10 rebounds and Smith finished with 15 points.
